fields.physical_description:
All samples start with the letter L.  They are not numerically in order or grouped.  Some are flashings other are the leaflets which accompanied the sets.  The decals are sticky paper which needed to be peeled off to be used.   All the smaller items are in plastic bags with the remains of gummed labels.  These bags were opened before arrival at the museum and most of the labels are torn.  As a result all parts will be given individual numbers.

1,2.  L55, Helicopter Flashings decal, printed in yellow and orange with black and white lettering.  CAPTURE COPTER ACTION MAN TRANSPORT COMMAND.  
3.  label on bag, torn, L75 QTY 2
4,5.  L152, length of printed card showing an outdoor scene of bushes, barbed wire, shell holes and detonator boxes.  At each end the card is grooved so it can be bent into shape.  It is part of the Control Headquarters.  Label sticking the two together L.152 QTY 2.  Eac is marked with the number as well 
6,7  L.155, Control Panel Screens Flashings decal, printed in colours to show radar screens, picture screens of rockets moving through space, aircraft, DAN GER  on two red panels, and dials.  Some parts have been cut out.
8.  label on bag, torn, L155 QTY 2
9,10  L184, M-41 (tank or personnel carrier) decal; printed in khaki, red, white and blue to show M-41 ACTION MAN.  On (7) three parts have been removed.
11.  label on bag, torn, L.184 QTY 2
12.  L.188, Badge Flashing decal, printed in colours to show an insignia of red, blue and yellow set on black.  Only one exists.
13.  label on bag, torn, L188 QTY 2.
14,15.  L279 Solar Hurricane cartoon or comic strip, marked Action Man Space Ranger and printed in black and white
16.  label on bag, torn, L279 QTY 2
17,18.  L280 Solar Hurricane Flashings decal, printed in turquoise, yellow and orange with black and white to show the name, control panel and trim.
19.  label on bag, torn, L280 QTY 2
20,21.  L322, Laser Range Detector Flashings decal, dark blue printed with white and yellow to show name and details
22.  label on bag, torn, L322 QTY 2
23.  L323, On Off Switch Flashings decal, dark blue printed with white and yellow
24.  label on bag, torn, L323 QTY 2
25,26.  L.567, Planetary Patrol Flashings decal, printed in orange and yellow with black red, blue and white to show the name Space Ranger and control panel dials.
27.  label on bag, torn, L567 QTY 2
28.  L586, Control Panel flashings decals, printed in dark blue, black, white and red.   Two panels have been removed from the strip.
29.  label on bag, torn, L586 QTY 2
30,31.  L590, leaflet printed in colours to show an action drawing on one side and photographs of Action Man equipment and uniforms on the other.  One as been partly cut with sections missing.
32.  label on bag, torn, L590 QTY 2
33,34.  Medical and Survival Kit Flashings, decal, printed in colours to 

show name and equipment parts.
35.  label on bag town, L606
36,37.  L722 Captain Cosmos Flashings decal, printed in colours to who name and equipment and flashings.
38.  label on bag, torn, L722 QTY 2
39.  L724, TOY OF THE DECADE decal, 1970-1980.  The medals were awarded by the National Association of Toy Retailers.
40.  L724, part has been cut away and what remains is the strip stting the assocaition's name.
41.  label on bag, torn, L724 QTY 2
42,44.  L730, Star Scheme Gifts leaflet, card printed in red and black on white to show the name and details of the scheme.  (42) has had part of the title cut away.
45.  label on bag, torn, L730 QTY 2.
46,47.  L740, Parking Tracks, shaped card printed in dark green, black and white with red to show title ACTION MAN TRANSPORT COMMAND.
(46) has been damaged with top surface torn and cut.
48,49.  L741, Computer and Radio Panel, shaped card printed in colours to show dials and switches.  (48) has been damaged with top surface torn and cut.  
50.  label on bag, L741 QTY 2
51,52.  L742, Radio and Radar Panel, matching L.741, shaped card printed in colours to show dials and switches.  (51) has been damaged with top surface torn and cut.
53.  label on bag, L.742 QTY2
54,55.  L.875 Air Blaster Start, printed card with large arrow marked in red and yellow; black dotted lines show where it needs to be cut out.
(one card is marked with the number the other is a clean copy)
56,57.  L881 Air Blaster Distance Markers, printed card to match L875 with black dotted lines to show where it needs to be cut out.  (one card is marked with the number and the other is a clean copy
58.59.  L884 Silver and Black Flashings decal, possibly part of Air Blaster.  (58) is numbered and has two parts missing, the other sheet is complete and unnumbered.
